description:
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cambridge University Hospitals (CUH) NHS Foundation Trust comprises Addenbrooke’s Hospital and the Rosie Hospital in Cambridge. With over 11000 staff and over 1100 beds the priorities of the Trust focus on a quality service which is all about people – patients, staff and partners. Recognised as providing ‘outstanding’ care to our patients and rated ‘Good’ overall by the Care Quality Commissioner, is testament to the skill and dedication of the people who work here. CUH’s values – Together- safe, kind, excellent – are at the heart of patient care, defining the way all staff work and behave. The Trust provides accessible high-quality healthcare for the local people of Cambridge, together with specialist services, dealing with rare or complex conditions for a regional, national and international population.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are recruiting a Band 6 Occupational Therapists for a rotational post at Cambridge University Hospitals in Cambridge.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a large department with a wealth of experience, we can offer you an exciting opportunity to continue your Occupational Therapy career. We will provide a supportive environment while helping cultivate your own individual style as a Therapist, enabling personal and professional development. We offer a diverse range of rotations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department of Medicine for the Elderly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Neurosciences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elective and traumatic Orthopaedics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rheumatology and Pain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stroke and Rehabilitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surgery and Oncology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Major Trauma&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hand Therapy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will provide dedicated and tailored assessment and treatments for patients. This will be done while illustrating clinical reasoning to members of the multidisciplinary team and promoting the role of Occupational Therapy. This will be done with opportunities for supervision with a Senior Occupational Therapist and peer support as you increase your autonomy as a practitioner.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are always excited to encourage service developments and provide a wealth of training and development opportunities. We provide flexible working opportunities including part time and full time. Occasional weekend working will be required after 6 months of employment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is subject to a satisfactory DBS clearance and as a result, you will be required to pay the associated fee of £40.00. This fee will be deducted from your second month’s salary.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held virtually on the 25th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits to you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer development opportunities and a wide range of benefits including on-site leisure facilities, shopping concourse, day nurseries and access to a great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details of our fantastic benefits please refer to the attachment below - CUH Benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note if you would like to discuss the required hours of this role further, you should approach the contact given. In some cases alternative working hours will be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome applications from the Armed Forces.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
